
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gzexe` yek file ejraee ra compress mikonad va on ra be shekle khod-bazgosha tabdil mikonad. Yani, vaghti file ejraee ejra shavad, aval az halat compress kharej shode va sepas ejra mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gzexe` --> File ra compress va khod-bazgosha mikonad.
    🔹 `gzexe -d` --> File ra az halat compress kharej mikonad (decompress).
    🔹 `gzexe -n` --> File asli ra pas az compress kardan hefz mikonad (naghes nemikonad).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gzexe myprogram

    🔹 File "myprogram" ra compress va khod-bazgosha mikonad.

    $ gzexe -d myprogram.gz

    🔹 File "myprogram.gz" ra az halat compress kharej mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gzexe myprogram
    $ ./myprogram

    🔹 Dastoor aval "myprogram" ra compress mikonad. Dastoor dovvom file compress shode ra ejra mikonad; file khod-bazgosha mishavad va sepas ejra misavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gzexe` command compresses an executable file and transforms it into a self-extracting executable.  That is, when the executable file is run, it first decompresses itself and then executes.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gzexe` --> Compresses the file and makes it self-extracting.
    🔹 `gzexe -d` --> Decompresses the file.
    🔹 `gzexe -n` --> Keeps the original file after compression (does not delete it).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gzexe myprogram

    🔹 Compresses the file "myprogram" and makes it self-extracting.

    $ gzexe -d myprogram.gz

    🔹 Decompresses the file "myprogram.gz".

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ gzexe myprogram
    $ ./myprogram

    🔹 The first command compresses "myprogram". The second command executes the compressed file; the file self-extracts and then runs.

